&lt;DIV&gt;Camby, I think where we differ is that you have this underlying assumption that it is only OK to attack a raid force if you intend to take the mob/encounter that they are preparing to engage.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I think that it is OK to attack a raid force simply because they are your enemy. "Winning" doesn't necessarily mean killing all of the enemy. It could be holding them up, delaying them, frustrating them.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I agree on point 2 "Can we reasonably engage&amp;nbsp;without causing&amp;nbsp;undo experience loss to our enemies ?" and this this is covered by the server ruleset already.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I also agree that "If you are beat, then stay beat and if you win, your enemy needs to bow out and do the same." However, I do see the use of succor, CoH etc. as perfectly valid tactics and not an indication that you are "beat".&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
